(320, 1, '2017-03-23 20:29:52', '2017-03-23 12:29:52', 'Vision  Mission of the School of Natural Sciences\r\n	We envision the School of Natural Sciences as a Center of Excellence for the advancement of science and technology through the development of biologists and health professionals who are competent, creative and research-oriented in their fields of specialization and guided by Christian values to serve society.\r\nSchool of Natural Sciences General Objectives\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Christian Spirit  To provide an educational program that would uphold human values in a learning environment characterized by a spirit of oneness, a climate of trust, openness and mutual respect.</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n		<li>Creativity  To conduct basic and applied researches, which are significant locally and globally. To find creative ways and means on how to operate as a self-reliant unit and sustain long-term growth and development.</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n		<li>Competence  To develop professionals by providing a learning experience through well-planned curricula in the analysis of the building units of life from the molecular level to higher levels of organization thus serving as a foundation for research and further studies.</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n		<li>Social Involvement  To assume responsibility over important health and environmental issues within the capacity of the school to perform. </li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'Vision Mission of the Natural Science Comittee', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'vision-mission', '', '', '2017-03-23 22:24:31', '2017-03-23 14:24:31', '', 0, 'http://localhost/?page_id=320', 0, 'page', '', 0),
